claim.claim-text:
1. A head gate element (2) comprising: 
a substantially flat (P) frame (1); 
a substantially rectilinear movable bar (10) mounted so as to pivot on a shaft (A) fixed to the said frame (1) and substantially perpendicular to the plane (P), so that the movable bar (10) can be situated in two extreme inclined positions, namely an open position (O) and a release position (D), as well as in an intermediate so-called closed position (F) in which the movable bar (10) is substantially vertical; 
fixed rigidly to one end (10a) of the movable bar (10), a locking fork joint (11) formed by two plates (11a, 11b), receiving a transverse slide (15) able to move in translation in the direction of the movable bar (10); 
a control bar (13) able to move in rotation about its longitudinal axis in order to control the possibilities of the movable bar (10) in the aforementioned three is positions (O, F, D), this control bar (13) being fixed in translation to the top part (3a) of the frame and extending between the two plates (11a, 11b) of the locking fork joint (11); 
the control bar (13) comprising locking means arranged to cooperate with the slide (15) of the locking fork joint (11), characterised in that the said slide (1 5) is guided in translation by guidance means situated on the internal face of each of the plates (11a, 11b).
